## Context

The manuscripts claim: "Bibliometric mappings of the climate and green
finance literature exist, built on corpora of 315 to about 3,300 documents
(Carè and Weber, 2023; Maria et al., 2023; Shang and Jin, 2023)". The
supporting material lives in
`deliverables/_shared/_includes/bibliometric-context.md`, which still
carries the "AI-generated, not human-reviewed" marker. Ticket 0152
web-verified the attributions (DOIs, corpus sizes, one phantom reference
replaced), but the comparison itself was never checked empirically: we
assert our ~31,000-work corpus is 10–100× larger and better validated
without testing whether it actually CONTAINS what the prior mappings
mapped.

The check strengthens the added-value case the RDJ-26561 revision needs
(editor ED-02, referee R1-18, tickets 0278/0283): "our corpus subsumes the
prior mappings' source populations" is a verifiable claim, stronger than a
size ratio.

## Relevant files

- `deliverables/_shared/_includes/bibliometric-context.md` — the comparison
  text; goal includes clearing its unreviewed-by-design marker
- `deliverables/data-paper/data-paper.qmd` and
  `deliverables/manuscript/manuscript.qmd` — where the sentence is cited
- `data/catalogs/refined_works.csv` via `pipeline_loaders` — our corpus
- Prior-mapping corpora: Carè & Weber 2023 (315 papers, WoS 2004–2021),
  Shang & Jin 2023 (2,311 WoS papers 2001–2022), Reis Maria et al. 2023
  (3,275 RePEc articles, STM), Deb & Chen 2024 (621 WoS), Singhania et
  al. 2023 (657 WoS)

## Actions

1. Verify each factual claim in bibliometric-context.md against the local
   PDFs (read-before-cite norm; PDFs staged per ticket 0152).
2. Empirical overlap check where feasible: reconstruct each study's query
   (they publish their WoS/Scopus search strings) and estimate what share
   of their corpus population our refined corpus covers — at minimum
   replicate the query against OpenAlex and match DOIs into
   refined_works. Report per-study coverage.
3. Write the result into the include (and vars if a number is cited);
   remove the unreviewed marker once human/author review done.
4. Draft the response-letter line for the added-value reply (feeds 0278/0283).

## Test

- Overlap-check script (if built) unit-tested on fixture DOI lists;
  numbers wired through the pipeline, not hand-pasted (provenance norm).

## Verification

- [ ] Every claim in bibliometric-context.md traced to a read source
- [ ] Overlap coverage numbers reproducible from an archived script output

## Invariants

- Methodological honesty; no hand-curated numbers in the papers;
  prose suite stays green.

## Exit criteria

- [ ] bibliometric-context.md verified, marker cleared after author review
- [ ] Per-study coverage/overlap result available and cited where the
      comparison is made
- [ ] Response-letter bullet drafted (feeds 0283)
